# Testing Conventions

## Test pyramid

| Layer | Annotation | Scope |
|-------|------------|-------|
| Controller | `@WebMvcTest` | MVC slice, mock services |
| Repository | `@DataJpaTest` | JPA + in-memory DB |
| Service | plain unit + Mockito | No Spring context |
| Integration | `@SpringBootTest` | Full context — use sparingly |

## Practices

- Use JUnit 5 (`@Test`, `@DisplayName`).
- Prefer `@MockitoBean` / `@MockBean` over manual mocks for Spring tests.
- For `@WebMvcTest`, disable security filters when testing non-auth logic: `@AutoConfigureMockMvc(addFilters = false)`.
- Assert HTTP status, JSON body, and headers — not implementation details.

## Integration tests

- Use **Testcontainers** for PostgreSQL/MySQL integration tests against real databases.
- Do not rely on H2-specific SQL in tests meant to validate production behavior.

```java
// GOOD — focused controller test
@WebMvcTest(controllers = ItemController.class)
@AutoConfigureMockMvc(addFilters = false)
class ItemControllerTest {
  @MockitoBean ItemService itemService;
  // mockMvc.perform(...).andExpect(...)
}
```
